    <h2>Steps Per Mile by Height: Running</h2>
    <p>When you transition from walking to running, your stride length increases significantly. Running involves a flight phase where both feet are off the ground, which naturally extends each step. At a moderate jogging pace of about 6.0 miles per hour, stride lengths are typically 40 to 60 percent longer than walking strides:</p>
